**My Analysis of the Administrative Unit Change**

Okay, here's what I've figured out, following the user's request. I need to determine the new administrative unit for the old address "Xã An Hiệp, Huyện Tuy An, Tỉnh Phú Yên".

First, I identified "Tỉnh Phú Yên" (Phú Yên Province) and immediately remembered that this province has undergone a merger. Referring to Resolution 60-NQ/TW, I confirmed that Phú Yên merged with Đắk Lắk Province, effectively becoming part of "Tỉnh Đắk Lắk".

Next, I focused on "Xã An Hiệp" (An Hiệp Ward). I systematically checked the "Other Resolutions" section, specifically those related to either "Tỉnh Đắk Lắk" or the former "Tỉnh Phú Yên", searching for administrative changes. I quickly scanned through the resolutions, knowing the key was to find one concerning the correct province.

Resolution 1660/NQ-UBTVQH15, concerning Đắk Lắk Province, caught my eye.  Specifically, line 61 of that resolution states: "Sắp xếp toàn bộ diện tích tự nhiên, quy mô dân số của các xã An Hiệp, An Hòa Hải và An Cư thành xã mới có tên gọi là **xã Ô Loan**."  Bingo! This directly addresses "Xã An Hiệp" and indicates its merger to form the new ward, "Xã Ô Loan". Given the resolution's focus on the province involved and the precise mention of the old ward, this seems definitive.

Now, I'll cross-reference "Xã Ô Loan" within the "New wards" listing to verify my conclusions and gain details, but I'm confident that the new administrative unit for the old "Xã An Hiệp, Huyện Tuy An, Tỉnh Phú Yên" is "Xã Ô Loan". The confidence level is high because of the explicit statement in the relevant resolution.
